Right now data uses the primary election as a placeholder. Beginning two weeks from election day, this can get updated daily with live data. Importantly, some of th areas of lowest primary turnout (e.g., Rainier Valley) also exceeded expectations (relative to expected general election turnout) more than any other area. Model-based predictions of turnout may struggle to capture the current (national) political environment and a more energized voting population. Primary turnout may be a useful metric to compare to, in additional to model-based predictions.

title: 2025 Seattle general election ballot return statistics
text:
Other options
Precinct-level turnout can be examined relative to projected turnout, primary turnout, and many demographic characteristics. Demographic characteristics include average age, racial makeup, educational attainment, dominant commute mode, owner vs renter occupied, average income, average home values, and dominant languages.
Voter-level data (i.e., whether an individual ballot has been returned) can be examined relative to projected turnout likelihood, recent voting history (e.g., primary), age, and gender.
